    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        CAB DOOR ADJUSTMENT - LOCK PILLAR ADJUSTMENT (Figure 48 )
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>LOCK PILLAR ADJUSTMENT (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1600648">Figure 48</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1600648" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1600648" filename="../figg16/G1600648.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 48. Adjusting Door Striker Pin</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. ADJUSTING SHIM</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DOOR STRIKER PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>3. DOOR LOCK PILLAR</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Door striker pin mounting provides for door adjustment by an enlarged hole and tapping block
                in lock pillar. Loosen pin to move pin up or down and in or out as required.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use spacer shim between striker pin and lock pillar for forward or rearward adjustment.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After final adjustment, tighten striker pin to 22-27 ft-lbs. (30-36 N&#8226;m). When
                adjusted: (1) door should contact door opening weatherseal all around with slight pressure but also
                without damage to seal, (2) door should latch, lock and release without undue effort, and (3) door
                should be rattle free when vehicle is in motion.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
